descript.purpose: Used to quide seed collection and use of Elnus Glaucus.The BreedBlock feature class contains polygon corporate data which depicts silviculture breeding blocks. This feature class is a product of the Pacific Northwest Region Coverage to Geodatabase Conversion Project in an effort to standardize data throughout the Region.

procstep.procdesc: Selected Ecoregions were clipped to the Umatilla Forest boundary. Selections of ecoregions was based on the availability of ELGL plot data. Resulting polygons were compared to sampled plot data for ELGL specie. This comparison resulted in another smaller subset of polygons being selected due to the lack of sample points in excluded polygons. Polygons were dissected by a line representing the Longitude line of 118 degrees 45 Minutes West. Polygons were attributed as E or W of this Longitude line.
Reprojected Feature set to a NAD83 Albers Equel Area Projection System specific to the States of Oregon and Washington
